IMPORTANT — SCOPE OF THIS MIT LICENSE

The MIT License above covers ONLY the software in this repository:
the Python extraction pipeline, schema definitions, validator, and
build tooling.

The Quranic text itself (the 6,236 ayat) is the literal word of God
revealed in the Qur'an and is in the public domain. It is included in
the database for matching and backfill purposes via the Tanzil-derived
canonical reference.

The i'rab, sarf, balagha, and fawa'id scholarly commentary embedded in
the generated SQLite database is derived from:

    الجدول في إعراب القرآن وصرفه وبيانه
    by Sheikh Mahmud Safi (محمود صافي)
    Published by Dar Al-Rashid (دار الرشيد), Damascus, 3rd edition (1416 AH / 1995 CE)

That commentary is the intellectual property of the late Sheikh Mahmud Safi
(may Allah have mercy upon him) and his publisher. This project preserves
and indexes that scholarship to make it accessible to students of Arabic
grammar and the Qur'an worldwide.

If you redistribute the generated database, you MUST credit Sheikh Mahmud
Safi as the source of the i'rab content. See NOTICE.md for the required
attribution text.
